# Voucher Generator & Tracking System

A full-stack voucher system where customers scan a QR code, land on a form page, submit personal details, and receive an auto-generated voucher code. An admin dashboard tracks redemptions, branch usage, and conversion analytics — hidden from directory brute-force tools like `dirb`.

---

## Recommended Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | Next.js 14 (App Router) | Full-stack React, API routes, SSR, great DX |
| **Language** | TypeScript | Type safety, better maintainability |
| **Database** | SQLite via Prisma ORM | Zero-config, file-based, perfect for single-server deployments. Can migrate to PostgreSQL later |
| **QR Code** | `qrcode` npm package | Generate QR codes pointing to the landing page |
| **Voucher Codes** | `nanoid` | Cryptographically secure, short unique IDs |
| **Charts** | `recharts` | Simple, composable React chart library |
| **Styling** | Vanilla CSS with CSS Modules | No external CSS framework, full control |
| **Auth (Admin)** | Cookie-based session with bcrypt | Simple, no external auth provider needed |

> [!TIP]
> **Why SQLite?** For a voucher system without massive concurrent writes, SQLite is ideal — zero setup, single-file database, easy backups. If you later need PostgreSQL or MySQL, Prisma makes migration trivial (just change the `provider` in `schema.prisma`).

