## User Review Required

### 1. Admin Dashboard Security Strategy

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Hiding the admin from `dirb`:**  
> `dirb` works by brute-forcing common directory names like `/admin`, `/dashboard`, `/panel`, etc. Our strategy uses **multiple layers**:
>
> 1. **Random route path** — The admin lives at `/gate/<random-hash>` (e.g., `/gate/x7k9m2p4`) instead of predictable names. This path is NOT in any standard wordlist.
> 2. **No client-side links** — Zero `<a>` tags or navigation pointing to the admin. It's completely detached from the public-facing app.
> 3. **Login-gated rendering** — Even if someone stumbles on the URL, they see a generic login form with no branding hinting it's an admin panel.
> 4. **Rate limiting** — API routes that power admin features are rate-limited.
> 5. **Custom response headers** — No `X-Powered-By` or framework leaks.
>
> **Do you want me to use a specific secret path, or should I generate a random one?**

### 2. Branch Configuration

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The system tracks which branch a voucher was redeemed at. I'll seed the database with some sample branches. **Please provide your branch names**, or I'll use placeholder names like "Main Branch", "Downtown Branch", "Mall Branch".

### 3. Voucher Code Format

> [!NOTE]
> Default voucher format: `VCH-XXXXXX` (6 alphanumeric characters, ~2 billion combinations). Want a different prefix or length?

